":"1040–1087","1128":"1128","Abt 1040":"about 1040","1087":"1087","1075":"1075","Aft 1087":"after 1087","1040":"1040","Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Wales":"Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Wales","Plouigneau, Finistère, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Finistère, Brittany, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert de Banastre I was born about 1040, in Plouigneau, Finistère, Brittany, France. He had at least 1 son. He died after 1087, in Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Wales."},"et":{"Abt 1040–Aft 1087":"umbes 1040–pärast 1087","1075–1128":"1075–1128","1040–1087":"1040–1087","1128":"1128","Abt 1040":"umbes 1040","1087":"1087","1075":"1075","Aft 1087":"pärast 1087","1040":"1040","Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Wales":"Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Wales","Plouigneau, Finistère, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Finistère, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1040–Aft 1087":"noin 1040–1087 jälkeen","1075–1128":"1075–1128","1040–1087":"1040–1087","1128":"1128","Abt 1040":"noin 1040","1087":"1087","1075":"1075","Aft 1087":"1087 jälkeen","1040":"1040","Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Wales":"Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Wales","Plouigneau, Finistère, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Finistère, Bretagne, Ranska"},"fr":{"Abt 1040–Aft 1087":"environ 1040–après 1087","1075–1128":"1075–1128","1040–1087":"1040–1087","1128":"1128","Abt 1040":"environ 1040","1087":"1087","1075":"1075","Aft 1087":"après 1087","1040":"1040","Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Wales":"Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Galles","Plouigneau, Finistère, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Finistère, Bretagne, France","lifeSummary":"Robert de Banastre I est né environ 1040, à Plouigneau, Finistère, Bretagne, France. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé après 1087, à Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Galles."},"de":{"Abt 1040–Aft 1087":"um 1040–nach 1087","1075–1128":"1075–1128","1040–1087":"1040–1087","1128":"1128","Abt 1040":"um 1040","1087":"1087","1075":"1075","Aft 1087":"nach 1087","1040":"1040","Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Wales":"Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Wales","Plouigneau, Finistère, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Finistère, Bretagne, Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Robert de Banastre I wurde um 1040 in Plouigneau, Finistère, Bretagne, Frankreich geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb nach 1087 in Prestatyn, Denbighshire, Wales."},"ht":{"Abt 1040–Aft 1087":"about 1040–af